captions.text:
Here are four very crazy, weird
ways that animals have sex.

Number one, cichlid fish
often reproduce by mouth.

The female begins by laying
eggs in the sand for a male
to inseminate.

She then quickly stores them
in her mouth for safekeeping,

sometimes before males
even get to inseminate.

Afterwards, she
may mistake spots

on a male fish's
tail for loose eggs
and will try to recapture them.

The male then inseminates
inside her mouth,

ensuring that any remaining
unfertilized eggs become
fertilized.

Number two, bedbugs mate
by traumatic insemination,

which is as traumatic
and painful as it sounds.

Male bedbugs will stab
the female's abdomen

with their needle-like penis
and insert sperm into the wound.

The female may be targeted an
average of five times this way,

sometimes by
different males, which

can leave scars and cut
her life short by 30%.

Number three, the
right sided garter

snakes mate in balls
of hundreds of snakes.

A female is found to
be more attractive when

multiple males are courting
her at once rather than when
she's alone.

As soon as she has
mated, she quickly

loses her attraction and
the rest of the male snakes

begin to look for
another female to court.
Sound familiar?

Number four, the
macaque monkeys mate
based on supply and demand.

If there are only a few
females to mate with,

the male will pay
for sex with her
by the currency of grooming.

However, if more females
are present at the time,

it brings down the price
of sex, and the males

will spend a much
shorter amount of time

grooming than they
would otherwise.

Know another species with
strange mating rituals?
Tell us in the comments.

Don't forget to subscribe to
Animalist for the latest animal
news, stories, and facts.
